00:08:10.700 --> 00:08:15.490
We could multiply all of these
constants-- c1, c2, ck, d1,

00:08:15.490 --> 00:08:17.260
d2, all the way to dn minus k.

00:08:17.260 --> 00:08:19.030
They could all be 0.

00:08:19.030 --> 00:08:20.790
Or there might be more
than one solution.

00:08:20.790 --> 00:08:25.690
In fact, if the only solution is
that all of these constants

00:08:25.690 --> 00:08:29.240
have to be equal to 0, then we
know that all of these vectors

00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:32.030
are linearly independent with
respect to each other.

00:08:32.030 --> 00:08:33.990
And if they're all linearly
independent with respect to

00:08:33.990 --> 00:08:39.919
each other, then we know that
they can be a basis for Rn.

00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:40.830
But we don't know that yet.

00:08:40.830 --> 00:08:43.460
We don't know that the only
solution to this is all of the

00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:45.000
constants being equal to 0.

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:46.240
So let's see if we can
experiment with

00:08:46.240 --> 00:08:48.270
this a little bit.

00:08:48.270 --> 00:08:50.820
If we take this equation, which
I just wrote down, we

00:08:50.820 --> 00:08:53.885
know that one solution is all of
the constants, the c's and

00:08:53.885 --> 00:08:55.110
d's equalling to 0, but
we don't know that

00:08:55.110 --> 00:08:56.460
that's the only one.

