00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:55.900
I don't even have to write
this is 0 here,

00:09:55.900 --> 00:09:57.800
that's a bit redundant.

00:09:57.800 --> 00:10:02.290
So what I have here is I have
some combination of the basis

00:10:02.290 --> 00:10:05.000
vector of V.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:08.880
So if I look at this, this is
some linear combination of the

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:11.650
basis vectors in V.

00:10:11.650 --> 00:10:17.030
If I call this a vector-- let
me call this some vector x.

00:10:17.030 --> 00:10:22.960
Let's say x is equal to
c1, v1 plus c2, v2 all

00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:28.650
the way to ck, vk.

00:10:28.650 --> 00:10:30.950
We know that it's a linear
combination of our basis

00:10:30.950 --> 00:10:36.630
vectors of V, so x
is a member of V.

00:10:36.630 --> 00:10:39.330
By definition, any linear
combination of the basis

00:10:39.330 --> 00:10:41.380
